After digging a bit into the problem, there seems to be an issue in {{OfbizPortletConfigurationStore}} or below.

Coming in from {{updateLocalDashboardItemProperties(Long, Map)}} we have the following property that requires saving:

key: gadgetConfig
value: "pivotTableType":"Timesheet","numOfWeeks":2,"reportingDay":1

{{toJsonString}} encodes this property by simply adding quotes around this string, so it becomes:

{noformat}
""pivotTableType":"Timesheet","numOfWeeks":2,"reportingDay":1"
{noformat}

{{JsonEntityPropertyManagerImpl.validateJson()}} chokes on this value since it is attempting to parse this as JSON.

The source of this value is the {{entity_property}} table:

{code}
select * from entity_property where entity_name = 'DashboardItemProperty';
{code}

{noformat}
id   |      entity_name      | entity_id | property_key |          created           |          updated           |                           json_value
-------+-----------------------+-----------+--------------+----------------------------+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------
 10704 | DashboardItemProperty |     10720 | gadgetConfig | 2016-03-08 10:25:46.041+01 | 2016-03-08 14:48:20.758+01 | {"pivotTableType":"Timesheet","numOfWeeks":2,"reportingDay":1}
(1 row)
{noformat}

Seems the conditions for hitting this bug are:

- a gadget that stores its configuration as JSON (as opposed to a simple value such as a string or number)
- add-on/gadget has a dashboard_module_complete_key configured in portletconfiguration table (versus a gadget_xml) - something to do with 'open social spec URL' (no experience with thisn personally)
